CloudProxy v1.5

This project depends on several third-party libraries. Before building
CloudProxy, you must download, build, and install these libraries. We have
provided a third_party directory under Code.


keyczar >= 0.71

keyczar will give a test error in the build step, but this is not important for
our use of the library. Note that you must have the openssl development
libraries installed for keyczar to build. See the instructions for keyczar for
more information.

> cd ${CODE}/third_party
> git clone https://code.google.com/p/keyczar/
> cd keyczar/cpp
> cd src && sh ./tools/swtoolkit/hammer.sh --mode=opt-linux --compat
> sudo su
# cd src && sh ./tools/swtoolkit/hammer.sh --mode=opt-linux --compat install
# exit


protobuf >= 2.5.1

> cd ${CODE}/third_party
> svn checkout http://protobuf.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ protobuf-read-only
> cd protobuf-read-only
> ./configure && make
> sudo make install


google-glog >= 0.3.3

> cd ${CODE}/third_party
> svn checkout http://google-glog.googlecode.com/svn/trunk/ google-glog-read-only
> cd google-glog-read-only
> ./configure && make
> sudo make install


gflags >= 2.0

> cd ${CODE}/third_party
> svn checkout http://gflags.googlecode.com/svn/ gflags-read-only
> cd gflags-read-only/trunk
> ./configure && make
> sudo make install


After installing these packages, follow the steps in creating_keys.txt to create
the required keys for CloudProxy, and run make to build the client and server
applications.
